paragraph.value: We inspect some pairs of events and entities in different kernels and list some examples in Table 5.  The pairs in Table 3 exhibit interesting types of relations: e.g.,"arrest-charge" and "attack-kill" form script-like chains; "911 attack" forms a quasiidentity relation (Recasens et al., 2010) with "attack"; "business" and "increase" are candidates as frame-argument structure.
